def count_bad_price_days(t, data):
    results = []
    for i in range(t):
        n = len(data[i])
        a = data[i]
        d = deque(a)
        m = d.pop()
        count = 1
        for j in range(n - 1):
            temp = d.pop()
            if temp > m:
                count += 1
            m = min(m, temp)
        results.append(count)
    return results
